"""E9. Create an area plot that visualizes `IS_Tuition` and `Fees` in a stacked manner. This chart shows the total cost of attendance."""

grouped = df.groupby('Year').sum()
grouped.drop(['OOS_Tuition'], axis=1, inplace=True)
grouped.plot.area()

"""E10. For each academic year, compute the percentage of the total cost due to fees and the percentage of the total cost due to in-state. The easiest way to do this is to create two new columns in your dataframe, one for each kind of cost (i.e., tuition and fees). You should see that the relative proportion for fees will increase over time. SBU can't change tuition, but it can play with the fees! """

df['IS_Tuition_p'] = df.loc['1999-2000']['IS_Tuition'] 
df['IS_Tuition_p'] = 100 * ((df['IS_Tuition']) / (df['IS_Tuition'] + df['Fees']))
df['Fees_p'] = 100 * ((df['Fees']) / (df['IS_Tuition'] + df['Fees']))
df

