"""E14. Use techniques from Module 20 to create two new columns in your dataframe: `IS_chg` and `OOS_chg` that show the percentage increase of in-state and out-of-state tuition over time, respectively, using the 1999-2000 academic year as the base value (i.e., 0%). Call `df.head()` to verify that this worked."""

df['IS_chg'] = df.loc['1999-2000']['IS_Tuition'] 
df['IS_chg'] = 100 * (df['IS_Tuition'] - df['IS_chg']) / df['IS_chg']
df['OOS_chg'] = df.loc['1999-2000']['OOS_Tuition'] 
df['OOS_chg'] = 100 * (df['OOS_Tuition'] - df['OOS_chg']) / df['OOS_chg']
df.head()

